section_purpose: To describe the evaluation metrics used in the experiments and list the baselines that Attn-JGNN is compared against.
key_points: The evaluation metric is root mean square error (RMSE) between estimated log countings and ground truth.
Neural baselines include BPNN and NSNet.
State-of-the-art approximate model counting solvers ApproxMC3 and F2 are also compared.
A time limit of 5,000 seconds is set for ApproxMC3 and F2 on each instance.

formulas: Root Mean Square Error (RMSE) between estimated log countings and ground truth

dependencies: Section 3.1 Attn-JGNN Framework for understanding the proposed method
Section 2 Preliminaries for background on methods
Section 4.1 Experiment Setup for dataset and other setup details
reproducibility_notes: Use RMSE as the evaluation metric for log countings
Compare against baselines: BPNN, NSNet, ApproxMC3, and F2
Set time limit of 5,000 seconds for ApproxMC3 and F2 solvers
